{{Quote|You're ''Domina Tagge''. ''The'' Domina Tagge. Head of the ''Tagge Corporation'', one of the galaxy's richest, I mean, most ''esteemed'' conglomerates&mdash;|[[Chelli Lona Aphra|Chelli Aphra]], to Domina Tagge|<ref name="Aphra 6" />}}
The '''Tagge Corporation''',<ref name="Aphra 6" /> also known as '''TaggeCo''',<ref name="Complete Locations">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> was a company owned and operated by the [[House of Tagge]]<ref name="Tarkin" /> that was headquartered within [[Tagge Space]].<ref name="Aphra 28">[[Doctor Aphra (2020) 28|''Doctor Aphra'' (2020) 28]]</ref> It was one of the largest<ref name="Aphra 35" /> and richest corporations in [[the galaxy]].<ref name="Aphra 6" /> The Tagge Corporation maintained [[mining]] operations, took part in [[foodstuff]] distribution, produced [[droid]]s, and developed weapons.<ref name="Aphra 35" /> The company was known to heavily invest in the research of [[Gungan]] technology.<ref name="Melee and Ranged Weapons">{{EncyclopediaCite|Melee and Ranged Weapons}}</ref> 

==History==
During the final [[Standard decade|decades]] of the [[High Republic Era]], the Tagge Corporation was based on the [[Core Worlds]] [[planet]] [[Tepasi]], but also had notable interests within the [[Corporate Sector]], being a signature member of its charter.<ref name="AcolyteVG" /> In the twilight years of the [[Galactic Republic]], it was notably involved in marketing and distributing food products. At the time, the company's [[TaggeCo. central strategy planning offices|central strategy planning offices]] were located on the Republic [[capital]] of [[Coruscant]]. Despite those [[Coruscanti]] ties,<ref name="Complete Locations" /> the company was headed by [[Sanya Tagge]] and [[Killian Tagge]], both of whom were loyal to the breakaway [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. Both made a play at securing a [[battle droid]] contract with the Confederacy via a droid designed by their daughter, [[Domina Tagge]], with that droid being her first ever design. However, both ultimately lost out on the contract, with the [[Tagge prototype battle droid]] never seeing usage.<ref name="Aphra 35" /> In the end, the Confederacy would lose the [[Clone Wars]] and, with its defeat, the [[Galactic Republic]] was transformed into the [[Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Tarkin" />

Despite Killian and Sanya's Separatist ties,<ref name="Aphra 35" /> the Tagge Corporation would begin work with the Empire<ref name="Tarkin" /> just as many former Separatist-aligned companies did.<ref name="MaskFear">''[[Reign of the Empire: The Mask of Fear]]''</ref> By [[3 ABY]],<ref name="Aphra 6 date">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of [[Doctor Aphra (2020) 6|''Doctor Aphra'' (2020) 6]] to [[3 ABY]].</ref> the company was headed by [[Lady]] Domina Tagge,<ref name="Aphra 6" /> who also led the company's [[Executive Board]]. Domino was protected by an [[Honor Guard (Domina Tagge)|Honor Guard]]. Domino was aided by her [[secretary]], [[Lapin Tagge]].<ref name="Boushh" /> The [[Gortus 4 colony|colony]] on the moon of [[Gortus 4]] signed over its rights to its moon to TaggeCo<ref name="Aphra 6" /> in 3 ABY,<ref name="Aphra 6 date" /> with Domina quickly ordering Lapin to have TaggeCo's [[Construction Division]] set up an ore factory on moon by the end of the week.<ref name="Aphra 6" />

A power struggle emerged when Domina's nephew, [[Ronen Tagge]], attempted to usurp control of the company. Allying with [[Crimson Dawn]] and [[Sana Starros' crew]], Ronen launched a [[Assassination attempt on Domina Tagge|full-scale battle]] for control of Tagge Space. In truth, however, [[Sana Starros]] had made a deal with Domina that she would help get rid of Ronen. Overplaying his hand, Ronen's efforts ended up failure when he underestimated Domina's [[aide]], [[Lapin Tagge]]. Having outright mentioned his alliance with Crimson Dawn and his attack having cost company lives, Domina was free to execute her nephew. Due to her help, Starros declared that her crew's debts to the Tagge Corporation were repaid and that she was owed a new ship.<ref name="Aphra 28" />

Many [[Standard year|years]] after the [[Battle of Jakku|defeat]] of the Empire, TaggeCo still existed. One of its subsidiaries, [[Galacti-Stok]], produced the [[Happy-Bore Medicated Dewormer]], a [[dewormer]] designed to control and rid [[happabore]]s of [[parasite]]s.<ref name="Survival" />

